#application-tests/src/test/resources/features/triforce/mosaic_post_with_body.feature
@mosaic @body_from_file
Feature: Mosaic API — POST with JSON body from file
  Demonstrates how to send a POST request where the request body
  is loaded from a JSON file under src/test/resources/testdata/.

  Background:
    Given the "mosaic" API is available

  @smoke
  Scenario: Register API key using request body loaded from a JSON file
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/apiKey?apiKey=MosaicService_apikey" with body from file "mosaic_register_apikey_request.json"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

  @regression
  Scenario: Enable RFQ synchroniser using request body loaded from a JSON file
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/rfqDataSynchroniserStatus?isEnabled=true" with body from file "mosaic_register_apikey_request.json"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |


#        application-tests/src/test/resources/features/triforce/mosaicapi.feature
@mosaic @regression
Feature: Mosaic API — Config and Toms Endpoints
  Validate Config synchroniser and API key endpoints, and Toms trade data retrieval
  against the live Mosaic QA API at mosaiclnqa01:5000.

  Background:
    Given the "mosaic" API is available

  # ── Config — API Key ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  @smoke
  Scenario: Register a valid API key returns HTTP 200 with success payload
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/apiKey?apiKey=MosaicService_apikey"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

  @regression
  Scenario Outline: Registering different API keys always returns HTTP 200
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/apiKey?apiKey=<apiKey>"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

    Examples:
      | apiKey               |
      | MosaicService_apikey |
      | testKey_001          |

  # ── Config — RFQ Data Synchroniser ──────────────────────────────────────────

  @smoke
  Scenario: Enable RFQ data synchroniser returns HTTP 200 with success payload
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/rfqDataSynchroniserStatus?isEnabled=true"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

  @regression
  Scenario: Disable RFQ data synchroniser returns HTTP 200 with success payload
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/rfqDataSynchroniserStatus?isEnabled=false"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

  # ── Config — TTA API Synchroniser ───────────────────────────────────────────

  @smoke
  Scenario: Enable TTA API synchroniser returns HTTP 200 with success payload
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/ttaApiSynchroniserStatus?isEnabled=true"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

  @regression
  Scenario: Disable TTA API synchroniser returns HTTP 200 with success payload
    When I send a "POST" request to "/api/Config/ttaApiSynchroniserStatus?isEnabled=false"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response root should match these values:
      | isSuccessStatusCode | true |
      | reasonPhrase        | OK   |
      | statusCode          | 200  |

  # ── Toms — GetFromDb ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  @smoke
  Scenario: GetFromDb returns trade records for a valid date range
    When I send a "GET" request to "/api/Toms/GetFromDb?from=2026-04-12T16:14:00.366Z&to=2026-05-12T16:14:00.366Z"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response array "root" should contain these records:
      | CustomerAccountCounterparty | SecurityCurrencyISOCode | TransactionId | BloombergFLVID |
      | JPA                         | EUR                     | 1002989       | 1005           |

  @regression
  Scenario: GetFromDb trade records contain counterparty, instrument and settlement fields
    When I send a "GET" request to "/api/Toms/GetFromDb?from=2026-04-12T16:14:00.366Z&to=2026-05-12T16:14:00.366Z"
    Then the response HTTP status should be 200
    And the response array "root" should contain these records:
      | CustomerAccountCounterparty | SecurityCurrencyISOCode | CounterpartyDecodedLongName | TransactionId | BloombergFLVID |
      | JPA                         | EUR                     | J.P. MORGAN SECURITIES LTD  | 1002989       | 1005           |



